article.description: — Rayshon Harrison had a season-high 24 points as Presbyterian topped Hampton 85-70 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Harrison scores 24 to lead Presbyterian past Hampton 85-70
article.linkText: Harrison scores 24 to lead Presbyterian past Hampton 85-70
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. -- — Rayshon Harrison had a season-high 24 points as Presbyterian topped Hampton 85-70 on Thursday night. Brandon Younger had 18 points and seven rebounds for Presbyterian (6-11, 4-9 Big South Conference). Winston Hill added 14 points and eight rebounds, and Kirshon Thrash had 11 points and 11 rebounds. Presbyterian totaled 45 second-half points, a season high. Raymond Bethea Jr. had 14 points and six rebounds for the Pirates (8-10, 7-6). Davion Warren added 13 points and seven rebounds, and Chris Shelton had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
